        <num>CCRP 811</num>
        <heading>811.  Receipt and recordation of verdict</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 811.  Receipt and recordation of verdict
If the verdict is correct in form and responsive to the indictment, the court shall order the clerk to receive the verdict, to read it to the jury, and to ask: &quot;Is that your verdict?&quot; If the jury answer &quot;Yes,&quot; the court shall order the clerk to record the verdict and shall discharge the jury.</p>
        </content>
